      },
      "learnable": false,
      "source": "data"
    }
  }
}
</VARIABLES>

<SUMMARY>
A linear utility model for responders that computes acceptance utility as a baseline plus a sensitivity-weighted difference between the offered share and a fairness benchmark. The fairness benchmark is determined by the participant’s proportional contribution to the total earnings. The model features two learnable parameters: baseline bias gamma and fairness sensitivity alpha.
</SUMMARY>

